benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07 cover removal of all tags, specific tags, empty tagDef, presence/absence of tags, and handling of extra parameters.
Non-Existent Resource: TC08 tests 404 when invoice item is not found.
Invalid Input/Format: TC09 (invalid UUID), TC13 (malformed tagDef), TC16 (partial tagDef), TC15 (malicious headers), TC18 (special characters in comment).
Authorization: TC10 (missing header) and TC11 (invalid token) cover auth errors.
Error Handling and Availability: TC12 (service unavailable 503), TC14 (very large tagDef), TC19 (integration/audit service unavailable).
Accessibility/Regression: TC20 checks accessibility of error messages and documentation.
gaps: Soft deletes: no explicit soft-delete behavior checks.
Rate limiting: no tests for rate limiting/throttling.
Caching: no tests for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios beyond missing/invalid auth.
Pagination: not applicable for DELETE in current scope; no paging tests for related endpoints.
Ambiguities in large tagDef handling (TC14) could be clarified with concrete thresholds.
recommendations: Add explicit 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient permissions beyond missing/invalid auth.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure the endpoint handles burst DELETE requests gracefully.
Add tests for caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) for endpoints returning 204 with no body.
Add tests for soft-delete behavior if supported (logical deletion vs physical deletion).
Clarify and standardize status expectations for extreme cases (e.g., TC14 large tagDef lists, TC19 integration failures) with concrete thresholds, and consider adding test variants for each outcome.
Extend accessibility coverage with more detailed screen-reader friendly error messages and documentation checks.
